texts.value: Transferrins are iron binding transport proteins which can bind two Fe(3+) ions in association with the binding of an anion, usually bicarbonate. It is responsible for the transport of iron from sites of absorption and heme degradation to those of storage and utilization. Serum transferrin may also have a further role in stimulating cell proliferation
Monomer. Part of a complex composed of SLC40A1/ferroportin, TF/transferrin and HEPH/hephaestin that transfers iron from cells to transferrin
Expressed by the liver and secreted in plasma
